    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fishing vessels with covered hulls and upswept prows that are fitted with mizzen-masts and mainsails with a boom and lowering gaff. These were used in the South Holland islands in the 18th and 19th centuries. The hull was covered to provide for a livewell for keeping live fish and bait.</Note_Text>
